# ============================================================================
# BOX (CUBE) - Quadric Surface Test
# ============================================================================
#
# DESCRIPTION:
#   A unit cube centered at the origin. While technically not a quadric
#   surface (it's a polyhedron), the box serves as a fundamental test case
#   for the OBJ parser.
#
# GEOMETRY:
#   - Dimensions: 1×1×1 unit cube
#   - Center: Origin (0, 0, 0)
#   - Bounds: -0.5 to +0.5 on each axis
#   - Vertices: 8
#   - Faces: 6 (each split into 2 triangles = 12 triangles total)
#
# OBJ FEATURES TESTED:
#   - Vertex positions (v x y z)
#   - Vertex normals (vn x y z)
#   - Texture coordinates (vt u v)
#   - Full face format (f v/vt/vn)
#   - Material reference (mtllib, usemtl)
#
# MATHEMATICAL DEFINITION:
#   A cube can be defined by the intersection of 6 half-spaces:
#     -0.5 ≤ x ≤ 0.5
#     -0.5 ≤ y ≤ 0.5
#     -0.5 ≤ z ≤ 0.5
#
# EXPECTED RESULTS AFTER LOADING:
#   - Triangle count: 12 (6 faces × 2 triangles per face)
#   - All normals normalized (length ≈ 1.0)
#   - Scene normalized to 6×6×6 bounding box
#
# ============================================================================

mtllib ./quadric_materials.mtl

# Vertices of the cube
v -0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5 -0.5 -0.5
v  0.5  0.5 -0.5
v -0.5  0.5 -0.5
v -0.5 -0.5  0.5
v  0.5 -0.5  0.5
v  0.5  0.5  0.5
v -0.5  0.5  0.5

# Normals for each face direction
vn  0.0  0.0 -1.0
vn  0.0  0.0  1.0
vn  0.0 -1.0  0.0
vn  0.0  1.0  0.0
vn -1.0  0.0  0.0
vn  1.0  0.0  0.0

# Texture coordinates (for completeness)
vt 0.0 0.0
vt 1.0 0.0
vt 1.0 1.0
vt 0.0 1.0

usemtl diffuse_white

# Front face (z = -0.5)
f 1/1/1 2/2/1 3/3/1
f 1/1/1 3/3/1 4/4/1

# Back face (z = 0.5)
f 5/1/2 7/3/2 6/2/2
f 5/1/2 8/4/2 7/3/2

# Bottom face (y = -0.5)
f 1/1/3 5/2/3 6/3/3
f 1/1/3 6/3/3 2/4/3

# Top face (y = 0.5)
f 4/1/4 3/2/4 7/3/4
f 4/1/4 7/3/4 8/4/4

# Left face (x = -0.5)
f 1/1/5 4/2/5 8/3/5
f 1/1/5 8/3/5 5/4/5

# Right face (x = 0.5)
f 2/1/6 6/2/6 7/3/6
f 2/1/6 7/3/6 3/4/6

